The developed sensor's analytical performance was assessed. A linear correlation was found between the fluorescence intensity of EP@CDs and NAR concentration, ranging from 0.0 to 2500.0 ng mL−1. The derived linear regression equation was F0/F = 0.0018C + 1.06, where F and F0 represent the fluorescence intensity of EP@CDs in the presence and absence of NAR, respectively, and C represents the concentration of NAR, with an associated regression coefficient of R2 = 0.9990. The emission spectra of the EP@CDs sensor in the presence of various NAR concentrations are shown in Fig. 3
                        A and 3B, while figure inset displays the calibration curves of EP@CDs sensor for NAR determination. The calculated LOD and LOQ values were 16.37 ng mL−1 and 49.1 ng mL−1, respectively. In addition, the performance criteria of the proposed fluorometric method were compared with other reported methods (Table 1
                        ).
